criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  patients older than 18 years;

          -  undergoing mechanical ventilation for more than 24 hours (in volume-controlled mode)
             and with readiness to run assisted ventilation;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  severe COPD with air trapping clinical suspicion;

          -  hemodynamic instability requiring inotropic or vasopressor support;

          -  any contraindications to esophageal catheter positioning
